# Why this patch exists
#
# undici's RequestHandler inherits from AsyncResource (node:async_hooks).
# This keeps async context alive for the lifetime of every request, which
# prevents the process from exiting cleanly when requests are still
# referenced by the async-hooks bookkeeping. It also leaks
# AsyncLocalStorage context between unrelated requests in tests.
#
# The patch removes the AsyncResource inheritance and replaces
# runInAsyncScope() with direct callback invocation. This is safe
# because node-addon-slsa never relies on AsyncLocalStorage propagation
# through undici response/error callbacks.
#
# Additionally exports MockInterceptor from types to support test usage.
#
# Re-evaluate when upgrading undici — the upstream may have changed the
# async-hooks integration or made it optional.

